article.headline: Cal Poly 86, UC Santa Barbara 79
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. (AP) -- Derek Stockalper had 19 points and seven rebounds as Cal Poly completed its first sweep of rival UC Santa Barbara in nine seasons Wednesday with an 86-79 victory. Five Mustangs scored in double figures for their first sweep of the Gauchos since the 1997-98 season. Cal Poly (13-10, 5-5 Big West) hit 15 of 30 from 3-point range and shot 51.9 percent from the floor (28-of-54). Dawin Whiten went 5-for-10 from beyond the arc, finishing with 15 points. Teammate Trae Clark, who hit four free throws in the final 25 seconds, had 18 points. Chaz Thomas scored 12 points and Tyler McGinn added 11 for the Mustangs. Alex Harris led UC Santa Barbara (15-8, 6-4) with 19 points. James Powell, Chris Devine and Cecil Brown each added 13 points for the Gauchos.
